The paper deals with Named Entity Disambiguation (NED) which is a task related to natural language processing and information retrieval. Therefore, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses graph-based knowledge bases and the use of statistical inference, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.DB (Databases). The use of machine learning techniques for NED also makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper involves benchmarking and evaluation of different approaches, which is relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
